				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/voct" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(392303); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=392303&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227558" alt="Voct" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=392303)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/voct" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(392303); return false;" >Voct</a></span> <span class="odate time_1385997825 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">02 Dec 2013 15:23</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1906518">
									

<p>Experiments that involve causing matter to be in places where it can't be&#8230; causing <em>bilocation</em>?</p>
<p>Shoot SCP-1247 with a large Nerf projectile from behind a cow (make it a carcass hanging from chains, so as to better control the situation). From our viewpoint, the Nerf projectile bounces off the carcsas and lands on the ground. From 1247's viewpoint, the projectile goes through the empty space adjacent to a Labeouf, and hits 1247. 1247 picks it up (without looking away from the test carcass) and holds it in his hand. The projectile continues to exist in both places at once until 1247 looks away from the carcass, at which point the one in his hand vanishes.</p>
<p>Now, try the experiment again&#8230; but this time, have 1247 continue staring at the carcass, and holding the projectile in his hand&#8230; and take the projectile that bounced off the carcass, and shoot it out of the Nerf gun a second time. Again, it (bounces off the carcass) / (goes through the Labeouf-adjacent space and hits 1247). Even though it's still in his hand. The Nerf projectile is now in three places at the same time: on the floor at the other side of the test chamber, on the floor at 1247's feet, and in 1247's hand.</p>
<p>Repeat the experiment again and again. As long as 1247 doesn't look away from the test carcass, we can keep generating more and more copies of the Nerf projectile. Have someone standing by to take the extra projectiles away for separate experimentation. Be aware that this experiment can only continue until 1247 gets too tired. Give 1247 some espresso, and put his head in a &#8230; what do you call it, one of those setups that will keep your head in a specific position. Continue generating Nerf projectiles. See how many we can generate.</p>
<p>Bring one of the copied projectiles back to the other end of the test chamber, and shoot it (off the carcass / through the Labeouf-adjacent space) again. Dip one end of the projectile in wet paint, and dab spots of paint on 1247 / the carcass. Physically modify the copies. Cut notches out here, add staples there, add some blue paint to this one, some red paint to that one. Keep generating Nerf projectiles.</p>
<p>Add RFID tags to the projectiles. Cut up one of the projectiles until it's little pieces of foam rubber; glue some of them to another intact projectile. Duplicate the projectile-covered-in-bits-of-other-projectiles.</p>
<p>Take a projectile. Duplicate it. Dip the one that bounced off the carcass in blue paint, dip the one that reached 1247 in red paint. Slice each of them in half, lengthwise, and glue each red half to each blue half.</p>
<p>Set fire to a pile of duplicate projectiles. Use the heat from the fire to boil water; use the steam to spin a turbine to generate electricity.</p>
<p>Put some hallucinogens in one of the projectiles. Duplicate the projectile. Give the duplicated hallucinogens to a class-D.</p>
<p>Stick a bullet inside one of the projectiles. Duplicate that projectile. Extract the duplicate bullet from the duplicate projectile, put it in a gun, use it to shoot an inconvenient public figure.</p>
<p>Turn off the lights in the test chamber, thus breaking 1247's line of sight with the carcass. What happens?</p>
<p>Set up a conveyor belt such that items can either bounce off a carcass or continue through a Labeouf-adjacent space and thereby cross the room to reach SCP-1247. Use the conveyor belt to duplicate the necessary components of a nuclear weapon. Rush the duplicate components to the other side of the world, reassemble them, obliterate a city. Turn off the lights in the test chamber. Is the wreckage still radioactive?</p>
<p>Use 1247 to duplicate a bacterial culture. Infect a class-D with the duplicate. Give the bacteria a while to reproduce themselves. Then turn off the lights in the test chamber. Is the D-class still infected?</p>

							</div>

								
					
