<p>Holy crap, Voct. This is incredible. You're a dangerous man.</p>
<p>I kinda feel guilty now that my explanation is so banal&#8230;</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">My&nbsp;version</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">I&nbsp;feel&nbsp;so&nbsp;inadequate</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">EXPERIMENT SCP-1247-E2-C-02</span><br />
Stimulus: A soft projectile was launched toward SCP-1247 such that it would be blocked by a horse's rear, but not by a perceived Shia LaBeouf.<br />
Result: The projectile was blocked by the rear. SCP-1247 reports seeing Shia LaBeouf &quot;snap&quot; into position to block the projectile at the point of impact.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">EXPERIMENT SCP-1247-E2-C-03</span><br />
Stimulus: Two soft projectile were launched simultaneously, such that one would be blocked by a horse's rear, and the other by the same horse's neck, but neither would be blocked by a perceived Shia LaBeouf.<br />
Result: Similar result to previous experiment. Shia LaBeouf reportedly moved nigh-instantaneously to block each projectile.</p>
<img src="http://s22.postimg.org/bc3gq6poh/beats_working_retail.png" alt="beats_working_retail.png" class="image" /></div>
</div>
</div>
<p>The trickiest thing I ever thought of doing with this guy was kidnapping the real LaBeouf to use him as a walkie-talkie. Your idea sounds like a proposal for SCP-2000!</p>

